IC: Wandering aimlessly through the almost, but never quite, calm forest, 
Mistra eventually found she had made her way right back to where she had 
started...the cave, and her pod. She knew what it was...yes. She knew her own 
name...but her identity was lost. 

Her tail whisked from one side to the other, annoyed at herself and her 
situation. &quot;Maximal...Predicon...I know both of those names well. I know...&quot; 
She whirled, lashing out with a paw at her pod &quot;I know that, but that which I 
am remains unknown..&quot;

With a heavy sigh, she layed down, head on her paws &quot;Why do I say this aloud 
I wonder...perhaps to see if I can indeed still speak aloud? Or perhaps I am 
trying to see if I am truely who I think I am...but who do I even think I am? 
Should it truely matter to me anymore..?&quot; She looked up to the blue sky &quot;Are 
there even others like myself on this planet? Will any of them know who I 
am..? Or will they just say such to gain my trust? Or am I alone...destined 
to meet my fate alone and be forever tortured by the information just out of 
my grasp?&quot;

She would eventually go offline if she was indeed alone on this planet. Of 
course, didn&#39;t all Cybertronians go offline sooner or later? Would it make a 
difference in the end? Was she even a Cybertronian...? Her form was that of 
an animal...yet it was one she was sure was abnormal. And she knew what she 
was sure no average animal knew...but then why did she not know? Two 
activation codes, both in her mind...Maximize, Terrorize. But which was her 
own? Was either of them even truely hers? 

&quot;I&#39;m beginning to think I was better off in the pod...&quot; she snarled to 
herself, stnading up once again. Where to go? What to do...?


